<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer2390589784065549733">Hunter Stockton Thompson was an American journalist and author, famous for his book <i>Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas</i>. He is credited as the creator of Gonzo journalism, a style of reporting where reporters involve themselves in the action to such a degree that they become the central figures of their stories. He is also known for his promotion and use of psychedelics and other mind-altering substanc</span>
  <span id="freeText2390589784065549733" style="display:none">Hunter Stockton Thompson was an American journalist and author, famous for his book <i>Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas</i>. He is credited as the creator of Gonzo journalism, a style of reporting where reporters involve themselves in the action to such a degree that they become the central figures of their stories. He is also known for his promotion and use of psychedelics and other mind-altering substances (and to a lesser extent, alcohol and firearms), his libertarian views, and his iconoclastic contempt for authority. He committed suicide in 2005. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2390589784065549733" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
